 A POPULAR hotelier in Ogun State who went missing on Monday night has been found dead inside his car trunk along Owode-Idi-Iroko Road. Alhaji Jimoh Bello, owner of Uncle J. Bee Hotel was found yesterday after three days of intensive search for him. It was gathered that the man left his home at Owode around 8:30pm on May 18 for Idi-Iroko but never got to his destination. The Nation gathered that his decompossing body was discovered after road users noticed blood stains underneath his car. Police Commissioner Kenneth Ebrimson said investigation was ongoing. 